<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="553" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,1221]" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1015,1041]" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">Remarks</emphasis>
. This species can be readily recognised by the presence of lateral processes on the aedeagal shaft and the thinner mesal pygofer process arising from the dorsal margin. 
<taxonomicName authority="Wei, Webb &amp; Zhang" authorityName="Wei, Webb &amp; Zhang" box="[881,1236,1051,1077]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Persea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="2" pageNumber="553" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dentatus">
<emphasis box="[881,1003,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">P. dentatus</emphasis>
Wei, Webb &amp; Zhang
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Wei, Webb &amp; Zhang" authorityName="Wei, Webb &amp; Zhang" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Persea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="2" pageNumber="553" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nanjingensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">P. nanjingensis</emphasis>
Wei, Webb &amp; Zhang
</taxonomicName>
also have lateral processes on the aedeagal shaft but the former has mesal pygofer processes forked distally and the latter has these processes broader and also they differ in the coloration. The unidentified female specimen of this genus from Darjeeling (
<collectingCountry box="[696,759,1159,1185]" name="India" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">India</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion box="[769,913,1159,1186]" country="India" name="West Bengal" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">West Bengal</collectingRegion>
) recorded by 
<bibRefCitation author="Wei, C. &amp; Webb, M. D. &amp; Zhang, Y." box="[1069,1260,1159,1185]" pageId="2" pageNumber="553" pagination="19 - 58" refId="ref5218" refString="Wei, C., Webb, M. D. &amp; Zhang, Y. (2010) A review of the morphologically diverse leafhopper subfamily Stegelytrinae (Hemiptera: Cicadellidae) with description of new taxa. Systematic Entomology, 35, 19 - 58. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 3113.2009.00480. x" type="journal article" year="2010">
Wei 
<emphasis box="[1121,1171,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">et al</emphasis>
. (2010)
</bibRefCitation>
is possibly the female of this species.
</paragraph>
